<title>USA: Corporate computer/software spending seen rising.</title>
<headline>Corporate computer/software spending seen rising.</headline>
<dateline>SAN FRANCISCO 1996-12-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Corporate spending on computers and software will rise 20 percent worldwide annually for years, fueling technology stocks, a Montgomery Securities research director said Tuesday.</p>
<p>Thomas Thornhill told investors at the securities firm's conference that he expects the worldwide technology spending to rise to more than $1.4 trillion in annual revenue by 2000 from about $950 billion now.</p>
<p>Thornhill said most technology bellwethers -- including International Business Machines Corp, Microsoft Corp, Intel Corp -- could still see their stocks rise in coming months, even though they are trading at record levels.</p>
<p>-- Kourosh Karimkhany, in San Francisco, + 1 415 846 5401</p>
